    <section class="page-hero">
        <h1>Introduction Agreement</h1>
        <p>Private household staff introductions coordinated by Trusted Household &amp; Childcare.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="agreement-section">
        <div class="agreement-card">
            <h2>Trusted Household Care Introduction Agreement</h2>

            <p><strong>Service Provider:</strong> SUNRISE GLOBAL SOLUTIONS - FZCO, operating the Trusted Household &amp; Childcare platform.</p>

            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> This agreement confirms the terms under which we introduce household staff candidates to a client family, including babysitters, nannies, housekeepers, elderly care support, household assistants, and related household-support roles.</p>

            <h3>1. Introduction Service</h3>
            <p>We assist the client by reviewing household requirements, identifying suitable candidates, coordinating candidate information, and arranging introductions where appropriate. We are an introduction and coordination service, not the direct employer of the candidate.</p>

            <h3>2. Candidate Privacy</h3>
            <p>Candidate CVs, photos, references, personal information, and contact details are confidential. The client agrees not to copy, publish, forward, or share candidate information with third parties without our written consent.</p>

            <h3>3. No Direct Bypass</h3>
            <p>If a candidate is introduced through us, the client agrees not to hire, employ, trial, or engage the candidate directly or indirectly outside our process. This applies whether the contact happens directly, through another family member, household employee, agent, or third party.</p>

            <h3>4. Introduction Fee</h3>
            <p>The client agrees that an introduction fee is payable if the client hires, employs, trials, or otherwise engages a candidate introduced by us. The exact fee is confirmed before any final placement or direct introduction.</p>

            <h3>5. Candidate Suitability</h3>
            <p>We use reasonable care when reviewing candidate information and matching candidates to the client’s stated requirements. The final hiring decision remains the client’s responsibility. The client should conduct interviews, request any required checks, and satisfy themselves before confirming an engagement.</p>

            <h3>6. Trial, Replacement, and Follow-Up</h3>
            <p>Any trial period, replacement support, or follow-up support must be agreed in writing before placement. Replacement support, if offered, applies only under the specific terms confirmed for that client and candidate.</p>

            <h3>7. Client Responsibilities</h3>
            <p>The client is responsible for complying with applicable local laws, visa rules, employment rules, salary obligations, accommodation requirements, insurance, medical checks, and any legal requirements connected to hiring household staff.</p>

            <h3>8. Limitation</h3>
            <p>We are not responsible for the client’s final employment decision, the candidate’s actions after engagement, or any employment-law, visa, immigration, tax, insurance, or household-management obligations of the client.</p>

            <h3>9. Acceptance</h3>
            <p>By requesting a private CV, candidate introduction, interview, trial, or placement, the client confirms that they understand and accept this introduction agreement.</p>

            <div class="agreement-actions">
                <a href="https://wa.me/971557862523?text=I%20accept%20the%20Trusted%20Household%20Care%20Introduction%20Agreement%20and%20would%20like%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20candidate%20introduction%20process." class="cta-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Accept via WhatsApp</a>
                <a href="/book" class="cta-btn secondary">Book Consultation</a>
            </div>

            <p class="muted center">This page is a practical introduction agreement template. Formal legal review can be added later if required.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

